#  Tools Overview

##  Overview
This section summarizes the main tools used throughout the learning path.

##  Tools Used

### Nmap
- Network scanning and enumeration

### Wireshark
- Packet analysis

### Burp Suite
- Web request interception

### Metasploit
- Exploitation framework

### SQLMap
- SQL Injection testing

### Gobuster
- Directory brute forcing

### John the Ripper
- Password cracking

### Hydra
- Brute force attacks

##  Key Takeaways

- Tools are essential but require understanding
- Each tool has a specific role in the attack/defense process
- Combining tools is key in real-world scenarios
